column3: DEATH Records Sorted by "Same" Surname & First Name

column2: Notes:  -Whenever there is an underline in the date, it means there was either none listed, it was illegible, or the date was in the binding.
-In the event we are able to get more death records from the church in Jakubany, we will begin a new file/link beginning 4-18-1900 as this one is long enough.
-"SAME" surnames spelled in various ways will be grouped together and sorted by first name of deceased and then by burial date.
-In regards to this special surname sorting, I will also will include various same first name spellings within the same group, such as Ana/Anna,
Catharina/Katalin, Elena/Helena/Ilona, Illes/Elias, Isidor/Feodor/Theodor, Istvan/Stephan, Miklos/Nicolaus, Susanna/Zuzana, and so on, under the english spelling if both are listed.
-To Identify a new major Surname listing/grouping (>1 like name), I will darken (bold) the first surname--this special marking will not transfer to the text link however.
-Hyphenated double surnames that are asterisked* will also be copied and appear under the second surname grouping too.
-For alphabetizing purposes, surnames beginning with Sz- or Zs- will be considered with just beginning with S or Z; the 2nd letter will be overlooked.
